sed method on more than 5,000\nindependent volumetric CMR scans from the UK Biobank study, achieving low error\nrates for missing basal/apical slice detection (4.9\\%/4.6\\%). The proposed\nmethod can also be adopted for assessing LV coverage for other types of CMR\nimage data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Nov 2018 22:07:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 8 Nov 2018 12:00:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-09"}
